<paragraph id="5A5136A0FF89FF8DFF55FBE1FECE5311" blockId="65.[212,382,1103,1127]" box="[212,382,1103,1127]" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="689AEAB2FF89FF8DFF55FBE1FECE5311" box="[212,382,1103,1127]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">Natural history</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5A5136A0FF89FF8DFF55FBD6FE055219" blockId="65.[212,1172,1143,1391]" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">
In Europe it has been reared from the fly 
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFD19FBD9FC3D53F9" authority="(Fabr.)" baseAuthorityName="Fabr." box="[664,909,1143,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Fanniidae" genus="Fannia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scalaris">
<emphasis id="689AEAB2FF89FF8DFD19FBD9FC8953F9" box="[664,825,1143,1167]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">Fannia scalaris</emphasis>
(Fabr.)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFC1BFBD9FBBB53F9" box="[922,1035,1143,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Fanniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Fanniidae</taxonomicName>
) when paralysed and used to provision the nest of the wasp 
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFCF0FB39FBE653D9" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[881,1110,1175,1199]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Oxybelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uniglumis">
<emphasis id="689AEAB2FF89FF8DFCF0FB39FBE653D9" box="[881,1110,1175,1199]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">Oxybelus uniglumis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) (
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFF5AFB19FEDD53B9" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[219,365,1207,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Crabronidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="3E7F4B51FF89FF8DFE05FB19FD8253B9" author="Chevalier L" box="[388,562,1207,1231]" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" pagination="93 - 96" refId="ref26472" refString="Chevalier L. 1925. Phora pygmaea Zett. Diptere mangeur de mouches. Bull Soc Sci Seine-et- Oise. 6: 93 - 96." type="journal article" year="1925">Chevalier 1925</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3E7F4B51FF89FF8DFDBFFB19FD6A53B9" author="Schmitz H" box="[574,730,1207,1231]" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" refId="ref28630" refString="Schmitz H. 1928 Verslag der Maandelijksche vergadering 5. September L. L. - Megaselia oxybelorum n. sp. Natuurhist Maandblad. 17: 121 - 122,131 - 132." type="journal volume" year="1928">Schmitz 1928</bibRefCitation>
). Females have been observed entering the nests of the wasp 
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFE43FB79FD315399" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[450,641,1239,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Cerceris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arenaria">
<emphasis id="689AEAB2FF89FF8DFE43FB79FD315399" box="[450,641,1239,1263]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">Cerceris arenaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) and in addition some males and females 
<emphasis id="689AEAB2FF89FF8DFBFEFB79FEAC5279" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">in copula</emphasis>
were also reported entering the nests of 
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFD76FB59FC5F5279" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[759,1007,1271,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Philanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangulum">
<emphasis id="689AEAB2FF89FF8DFD76FB59FC5F5279" box="[759,1007,1271,1295]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="171">Philanthus triangulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F. (
<taxonomicName id="9DEE4D23FF89FF8DFBA0FB59FF4D5259" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Philanthidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Philanthidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="3E7F4B51FF89FF8DFE95FAB9FE425259" author="Polidori C &amp; Disney RHL &amp; Andrietti F" box="[276,498,1303,1327]" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" pagination="93 - 95" refId="ref28397" refString="Polidori C, Disney RHL, Andrietti F. 2001. Some behavioural observations on Megaselia oxybelorum (Diptera: Phoridae), a new kleptoparasite of Cerceris arenaria (Hymenoptera: Sphecoidea: Philanthidae). Br J Entomol Nat Hist. 14: 93 - 95." type="journal article" year="2001">Polidori et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3E7F4B51FF89FF8DFE7EFAB9FD895259" author="Polidori C &amp; Papadia C &amp; Disney RHL &amp; Andrietti F" box="[511,569,1303,1327]" pageId="65" pageNumber="171" pagination="1969 - 1982" refId="ref28499" refString="Polidori C, Papadia C, Disney RHL, Andrietti F. 2006. Behaviour and activity patterns of the scuttle fly Megaselia oxybelorum Schmitz (Diptera: Phoridae) at nest aggregation of two host digger wasps (Hymenoptera: Crabronidae). J Nat Hist. 40: 1969 - 1982." type="journal article" year="2006">2006</bibRefCitation>
). In the latter case the males left the nests soon after entry but the females only left some time later, suggesting that they had been ovipositing before leaving.
</paragraph>
